    "desc": "Explore Case Western Reserve University: the top-ranked school in Ohio and one of the best research universities in the U.S. Located in Cleveland, Ohio.",
    "text": "MENU\nAt Case Western Reserve University, we think big.\nBut we don't just think, we do.\nOn campus and around the world, we explore and discover, engage and invent.\nMost of all, we make a difference—especially when it appears impossible.\nThe CWRU Difference\n%\nof our undergrads take part in experiential learning, including research, co-ops and internships\nstudent organizations where you can pursue your passions, give back to your community and make amazing new friends\n+\narts, cultural, medical and academic institutions within 1 mile, making our campus a vibrant place to study, work and live\nResearch and Innovation\n01\n02\n03\n04\n05\nA Benefit of Stress?\nIn a new study, CWRU researchers found that a measure of stress might actually benefit the immune system.\nFind out more about their research.\nStudent Spotlight\n1,300+\nclinical hours for our undergraduate nursing students\n2x\nthe clinical hours most nursing schools provide\n200\ncommunity organizations and agencies where students get hands-on experience\n“CWRU is a wonderful place to get involved in things you’ve never done before. I had no healthcare or leadership experience, and now those are my two most rewarding parts of college.“\n– Sophie V. (CWR '22), nursing, Undergraduate Student Government President\n01/04\nPrev\nNext\nNews and Updates\nWomen’s soccer team falls to Johns Hopkins 2-1 in NCAA Division III Championship, finishes season national runner-up\nCase Western Reserve University battled through 90 minutes of intense soccer, but the fourth-ranked women’s soccer team ultimately came up short...\nWomen’s soccer team continues historic season today in NCAA Division III Championship semifinals\nDown by two goals with just 32 minutes left in the quarterfinals of the 2022 NCAA Division III Women’s Soccer Championship, many teams would start...\n3 things to do in Cleveland in December\nThe temperatures may be dropping in Northeast Ohio, but there are still plenty of opportunities to get out and enjoy Cleveland.\nSee All News\nTOP\n10900 Euclid Ave. Cleveland, OH 44106\n216.368.2000\n© 2022 Case Western Reserve University\nLegal Notice | Privacy Statement\nCampus Safety\nCanvas\nCareers\nDiversity\nDirectory\nFinancial Aid\nGive to CWRU\nLibraries\nMedia\nStudent Information System\nUniversity Technology\nWebmail",
